## Test Anti-Pattern Audit: `ProductCatalogTests.cs`

### Summary

| Severity | Count |
|----------|-------|
| **Critical** | 6 |
| **High** | 1 |
| **Medium** | 2 |

This is a textbook **coverage-touching** test class. Every public method on `ProductCatalog` is invoked (achieving the 95% coverage number), but almost nothing is verified. These tests will pass even if the production code is completely broken — they only prove the code doesn't throw.

---

### Critical Findings

#### 1. Coverage Touching (Systemic)

The entire class follows the pattern: call method → no assertion (or only `Assert.IsNotNull`). 6 of 10 tests have **zero assertions**; the remaining 4 use `Assert.IsNotNull` which only proves a reference isn't null — not that behavior is correct.

#### 2. No Assertions — `AddProduct_Works` (line 17)

```csharp
// BEFORE — proves nothing
_catalog.AddProduct(product);

// FIX — verify the product was actually stored
_catalog.AddProduct(product);
var stored = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.AreEqual("Widget", stored?.Name);
Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, stored?.Price);
```

#### 3. No Assertions — `UpdatePrice_Works` (line 32)

```csharp
// BEFORE — price may not have changed
_catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);

// FIX — verify the price was updated
_catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);
var updated = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.AreEqual(14.99m, updated!.Price);
```

#### 4. No Assertions — `RemoveProduct_Works` (line 39)

```csharp
// BEFORE — product may still exist
_catalog.RemoveProduct("SKU-001");

// FIX — verify deletion
_catalog.RemoveProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.IsNull(_catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001"));
```

#### 5. No Assertions — `GetProductCount_Works` (line 63)

```csharp
// BEFORE — count is discarded
var count = _catalog.GetProductCount();

// FIX — verify the count
Assert.AreEqual(0, count);
```

#### 6. No Assertions — `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` (line 69)

This is the most dangerous one — `ApplyBulkDiscount` has real arithmetic (`Price * (1 - fraction)`) that could easily regress.

```csharp
// BEFORE — discount math is never verified
_catalog.ApplyBulkDiscount(0.10m);

// FIX — verify prices were reduced by 10%
_catalog.ApplyBulkDiscount(0.10m);
Assert.AreEqual(8.991m, _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001")!.Price);
Assert.AreEqual(17.991m, _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-002")!.Price);
```

#### 7. No Assertions — `ImportFromCsv_Works` (line 85)

